This pack has Hardcore Darkness and Infernal Mobs in it! You should probably make haste to find shelter before night falls...

§lMake sure to check your keybindings!
§rThe default keybinding for the questbook is Grave (`).

AromaBackup is included in this modpack by default.

To change directory, frequency, and the number of backups to keep, you'll need to edit the mod's config file located at '.minecraft/config/aroma1997'.

JourneyMap data is §cnot§r backed up by AromaBackup, so be sure to back it up yourself if you're afraid of losing it.

Better Questing has several nice commands for the questbook. You'll need to have cheats enabled, or have OP status on the server you're playing on to use them however.

/bq_admin default load
Use this to update your questbook after a modpack update.

/bq_admin edit
Toggles editing quests. Pressing RMB on the quest will open a context menu to share it or copy its ID.

/bq_admin reset all <Player Name>
Resets ALL quests from the specified player. Not reversable.

/bq_admin reset <Quest ID> <Player Name>
Resets a specific quest

/bq_admin complete <Quest ID> <Player Name>
Completes a specific quest. Use if a quest is broken.

/bq_admin default save
Saves changes to the questbook after editing.

/bq_admin hardcore
Enabled Better Questing Hardcore Mode. You have 3 lives, make them count!
FTB Utilities is provided, allowing easy chunk loading in singleplayer or multiplayer!

As you've probably noticed, normal Minecraft Wood and Stone tools are disabled. You'll have to use Tinkers Construct tools throughout this entire modpack.

Keep on the lookout for Pam's Harvestcraft gardens. They're a good source of seeds.

If you check the recipes for flint in JEI, you'll notice there's a shapeless recipe for 1 flint from 3 gravel.

When you make your first GregTech mortar, you'll be able to make flint 1:1 from gravel.

Take some free flint for tool repairs.
The crafting recipe is no longer 4 Wood Planks. Don't blame me, blame GregoriusT or the GregTech CEu team!

Noticed the difference between the quest borders yet?
The quests with jagged edges are main quests - they are required for progression.

The quests with smooth edges are optional quests, and are not required for progression. They could still provide useful items as rewards though!
Now that you've (hopefully) got a shelter and a crafting table, you should make some basic tools. You shouldn't need to make a ton of these since you'll gain access to Tinkers tools very soon.
Fruit trees can be a decent source of food early game. You can make juice, smoothies, and other foods from the fruit. Or you could just eat it.

Food and hunger will be your biggest concern early game. Spice of Life's increased hunger drain has been disabled however. The hunger will drain at the normal Minecraft rate.

Collect a few seeds and you'll be rewarded with some carrots to plant.

Finally! Furnaces...

Since you're unable to make charcoal in the furnace, I'll be kind and give you enough to smelt a full stack of items. Enjoy!
You'll need a sword to defend yourself against the local wildlife and monsters. GregTech flint swords come with the upside of free Fire Aspect! Enjoy not needing to cook your food.
You should gather enough wool to make a bed. GregTech has changed the recipe, so be sure to check JEI for the updated recipe.

After a long and ard arduous journey microcrafting, you can finally make a bed! This is only the beginning. however. You can use the dye with your freshly made bed in a crafting grid to dye it any color you'd like.

After this quest is completed, Tier 0 will be unlocked.
Did you plant those carrots? I hope you did!
Tinkers Construct tools are the only tools viable in the early game. Go craft all the Tinkers tool stations to proceed.

You'll need to make blank patterns to craft all of the Tinkers stations. As you can see from JEI, the normal recipe is disabled. Blank patterns now require 4 paper to craft. There are 2 ways to get paper, either from chad from sugarcane, or wood pulp.

The Healing Axe is a very powerful item. Not only does it function with the speed of a diamond axe, it has infinite durability and will passively restore hunger and saturation when held in the main hand or offhand.
